2026-05-16 09:13:01 | DEBUG | strands_evaluation.instrumentation.agent_plugins | Model response #7 [role=assistant block=1 tool_use] execute_ideal({"intent": "Compute correlations for freshwater vs marine between summer rainfall (Jun-Jul-Aug totals, imputed medians per station-month) and beach exceedance rate (fraction of Violation==yes) for 2007-2009. Return which beach type has higher Pearson correlation.", "dataset_id": "kramabench-environment-hard-14", "code": "import pandas as pd, numpy as np\nfrom pathlib import Path\nbase = Path('/home/ec2-user/eval_eqa/.sandbox_isolated/task_1507774_1778922681902/kramabench-environment-hard-14/files')\n\ndef read_local(name):\n    return pd.read_csv(base/name)\n\n# Load water testing\nwater = []\nfor y in [2007,2008,2009]:\n    df = read_local(f'water-body-testing-{y}.csv')\n    df['Year']=df['Year'].astype(int)\n    water.append(df)\nwater = pd.concat(water, ignore_index=True)\nwater['Violation']=water['Violation'].astype(str).str.lower()\nwater['is_violation'] = water['Violation'].map({'yes':1,'no':0}).astype(float)\n\nexceed = water.groupby(['Year','Beach Type Description'])['is_violation'].mean().reset_index(name='exceedance_rate')\n\n# Load precipitation\nprec_files = {\n    'Boston': 'monthly_precipitations_boston.csv',\n    'Chatham': 'monthly_precipitations_chatham.csv',\n    'Amherst': 'monthly_precipitations_amherst.csv',\n    'Ashburnham':'monthly_precipitations_ashburnham.csv'\n}\nmonths=['Jun','Jul','Aug']\nprec={}\nfor st,fname in prec_files.items():\n    df = read_local(fname)\n    df['Year']=df['Year'].astype(int)\n    for m in months:\n        df[m]=pd.to_numeric(df[m].replace('M', np.nan), errors='coerce')\n    # impute per station-month median across non-missing years\n    for m in months:\n        med = df[m].dropna().median()\n        df[m]=df[m].fillna(med)\n    prec[st]=df.set_index('Year')\n\n# rainfall vectors (average across stations)\nyears=[2007,2008,2009]\n\ndef summer_total(stations):\n    stacks=[]\n    for st in stations:\n        tmp = prec[st].loc[years, months].sum(axis=1)\n        stacks.append(tmp)\n    mat = pd.concat(stacks, axis=1)\n    return mat.mean(axis=1)\n\nrain_fresh = summer_total(['Boston','Chatham','Amherst','Ashburnham'])\nrain_marine= summer_total(['Boston','Chatham'])\n\n# get exceedance by beach type\npivot = exceed[exceed['Year'].isin(years)].pivot(index='Year', columns='Beach Type Description', values='exceedance_rate')\n# identify columns\ncols = list(pivot.columns)\nfresh_col = [c for c in cols if 'fresh' in str(c).lower()][0]\nmarine_col = [c for c in cols if 'marine' in str(c).lower()][0]\nex_fresh = pivot.loc[years, fresh_col]\nex_marine= pivot.loc[years, marine_col]\n\ncorr_fresh = np.corrcoef(rain_fresh.values, ex_fresh.values)[0,1]\ncorr_marine= np.corrcoef(rain_marine.values, ex_marine.values)[0,1]\n\ncorr_fresh, corr_marine, fresh_col, marine_col, rain_fresh.to_dict(), ex_fresh.to_dict()"}) [toolUseId=call_MMnubEabKEawTztUrCep5B4H]
